\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl280\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs42 \cf3 		In a small saucepan, heat half-and-half to 175\'b0. Remove from the\
		heat; add lavender. Cover and steep for 20 minutes. Strain,\
		discarding lavender.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs50 \cf3 		\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl280\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs42 \cf3 		Return to the heat; stir in sugar until dissolved. Whisk a small\
		amount of the hot mixture into the egg yolks. Return all to the pan,\
		whisking constantly. Cook and stir over low heat until mixture\
		reaches at least 160\'b0 and coats the back of a metal spoon.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs50 \cf3 		\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl280\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs42 \cf3 		Remove from the heat. Cool quickly by placing pan in a bowl of ice\
		water; stir for 2 minutes. Stir in whipping cream. Press waxed paper\
		onto surface of custard. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.\
		
